query.result:
76 As they are ruminating dwellings 77 the goats, staying rapid and proud 78 over the peaks before they are fed,
79 silent in the shadow, while the sun burns, 80 watched by the shepherd, who on the rod 81 leaned has and to them of rest serves;
82 and as the herd that outside shelters, 83 along its flock quiet spends the night, 84 watching because a beast does not scatter it;
85 such were we all three huddled, 86 I like a goat, and he like shepherds, 87 sheltered on this side and that by high cave.

88 Little could appear there of the day outside;
89 but, through that little, I saw the stars
90 of their brightness and more clear and larger.

103 To please myself in the mirror, here I adorn myself;
104 but my sister Rachel never tires
105 of her mirror, and sits all day.

106 She is eager to see of her beautiful eyes
107 as I of adorning myself with the hands;
108 her seeing it, and me working at it satisfies.

