130 Tratto t’ho qui con ingegno e con arte;
131 lo tuo piacere omai prendi per duce;
132 fuor se’ de l’erte vie, fuor se’ de l’arte.

query.result:
130 I have led you here with skill and with art;
131 your pleasure now take for guide;
132 outside you are of the steep ways, outside you are of the art.

133 See the sun which in front to you shines;
134 see the grasses, the flowers and the small shrubs
135 that here the earth alone from itself produces.
